                    <span>I bot this book for a friend who is a Jr-Mid level network (Unix) admin., who needed advice on this topic. This book does cover all the necessary topics. It's understandable, not overwhelming, and, as the TOC shows, covers lots of useful, relevant topics. It's also very practical. Worth buying!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Not worth the O'reilly name</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
